.TH "TD\-CONVERT" "1" "2026" "TARDIS Manual"
.SH NAME
td\-convert \- convert a date between formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]td convert\f[R] \f[I]INPUT\f[R] \f[B]\-\-to\f[R] \f[I]FORMAT\f[R]
[\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]td convert\f[R] takes a date expression or formatted date string
and re\-renders it in the target format specified by \f[B]\-\-to\f[R].
.PP
When \f[B]\-\-from\f[R] is provided, the input is parsed according to
that strptime pattern.
When omitted, \f[B]td\f[R] attempts to auto\-detect the input format by
trying RFC 3339, ISO 8601, natural\-language parsing, and epoch
timestamps (with or without the **\[at]** prefix).
.PP
Built\-in format names accepted by \f[B]\-\-to\f[R] (and
\f[B]\-\-from\f[R]):
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]iso8601\f[R] \[en] ISO 8601 format
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]rfc3339\f[R] \[en] RFC 3339 format
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]rfc2822\f[R] \[en] RFC 2822 format
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]epoch\f[R] / \f[B]unix\f[R] \[en] Unix timestamp (seconds since
epoch)
.PP
Any strftime pattern or preset name from the config file is also
accepted.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-\-from\f[R] \f[I]FORMAT\f[R]
Input format (strptime pattern or preset name).
Auto\-detected if omitted.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-to\f[R] \f[I]FORMAT\f[R]
Output format (required).
Accepts strftime patterns, preset names, or built\-in names: iso8601,
rfc3339, rfc2822, epoch, unix.
.TP
\f[B]\-j\f[R], \f[B]\-\-json\f[R]
Output as a JSON object.
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\-\-no\-newline\f[R]
Suppress the trailing newline.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-now\f[R] \f[I]DATETIME\f[R]
Override the current time (RFC 3339).
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\-\-timezone\f[R] \f[I]TZ\f[R]
Timezone for resolution (IANA/Olson ID).
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\-\-verbose\f[R]
Print verbose diagnostics to stderr.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\-\-help\f[R]
Print help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Convert a natural\-language expression to epoch:
.IP
.EX
td convert \[dq]2025\-06\-24\[dq] \-\-to epoch \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Convert from ISO 8601 to a custom format:
.IP
.EX
td convert \[dq]2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z\[dq] \-\-to \[dq]%d/%m/%Y %H:%M\[dq] \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Auto\-detect input and convert to RFC 2822:
.IP
.EX
td convert \[dq]next friday\[dq] \-\-to rfc2822 \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Convert a bare epoch timestamp:
.IP
.EX
td convert 1719244800 \-\-to \[dq]%Y\-%m\-%d\[dq] \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Convert with explicit input format:
.IP
.EX
td convert \[dq]24/06/2025\[dq] \-\-from \[dq]%d/%m/%Y\[dq] \-\-to iso8601 \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
JSON output:
.IP
.EX
td convert \[dq]tomorrow\[dq] \-\-to epoch \-\-json \-t UTC
.EE
